		<div id="comment_body_64899393"><p>While this is very cool, I see that Raspberry Pi 5's internal PCIe bussing is Gen 2.0 x1.  So although it supports NVMe SSDs from a pure connectivity standpoint and that in and of itself has a lot of value, they will run a lot slower than in your typical modern x86 mobo.</p><p>Not being disparaging at all.  Raspy Pi 5s are awesome and this is expected, so I looked up this info as I was interested to know the actual throughput one could expect.</p></div>
