	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64899407"><p>PCIe2 is still blazing fast for a storage interlink compared to what was common not that many years ago. There are lots of application where it will be great and more suitably compact than SATA cables, its also 'simpler' than SATA in the m2 format.</p><p>That said Pis are getting more 'expensive' and it seems like the trend is more and more to off the shelf parts vs, make something with the GPIO pins. At some point they are going to need to decide how to target these products or maybe create some more stratification, because I don't know what it is anymore.  Is it hobby kit, or are they "consumer ARM PC parts"</p></div>
	</div>

