		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64899491"><p>The problem is the Pi was originally designed to be produced as cheaply as possible and to be a tool for students. Write a few lines of code to toggle an IO pin or collect data from a sensor. People kept asking for more powerful designs and the Pi foundation obliged. The first Pi had a composite video output and today people use them for playing 4k video at 60hz.</p><p>Luckily it opened the door for many clones to appear and RISC-V is getting attention now to free up licensing from ARM.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64899491">

