		on Monday October 28, 2024 @08:45AM (<span class="ind"></span><a rel="nofollow" href="//hardware.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23501745&amp;cid=64899461">#64899461</a>)
		<small> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64899461"><p>The Raspberry Pi 5 doc states PCIe 3.0 mode isn't stable, which is why it's not enabled by default:</p><p> <i>The Raspberry Pi 5 is not certified for Gen 3.0 speeds, and connections to PCIe devices at these speeds may be unstable.</i> </p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64899461">
