	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64899433">The branded products are nice for ensuring maximal compatibility.  But as <a href="https://www.youtube.com/@JeffGeerling" title="youtube.com">Jeff Geerling on Youtube</a> [youtube.com] has <a href="https://github.com/geerlingguy/raspberry-pi-pcie-devices/tree/master" title="github.com">documented extensively</a> [github.com] since the Pi5 came out, there are lots of M.2 HATs out there that work really well.  Many, by breaking modestly from the official HAT specification, allow for substantially larger SSDs - up to a 2280 module size.</div>
	</div>

